…As FEC
Goes Into Closed-Door Meeting By Chibuike
Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – President
Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday presided over the valedictory session of the
Federal Executive Council meeting. The meeting started
around 11.03am with the rendition of the National anthem as the President
arrived the Council chamber of the State House, Abuja. Opening Muslims prayer
was said by the Minister of Environment, Suleiman Hassan while Christian
opening prayer was offered by the Minister of Niger Delta Affairs, Usani Uguru. The meeting immediately
went into closed doors meeting after the prayers. It was learnt that
journalists would be invited in to cover the valedictory session proper. New hands are expected to
be injected into the next cabinet as the inauguration of the second term
administration of President Buhari comes up on 29th May, 2019.